Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over half the @peri peri seasoning{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell peppers{2} lengthways and discard the core and seeds.

Lay the pepper halves, cut-side up, onto a baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop the @garlic cloves{3}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Add the parcel to the same #baking tray{} as the pepper.

Roast the pepper and garlic parcel on the middle shelf until starting to soften, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @tomato puree{30%g} and remaining peri peri seasoning. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the lentils, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%pinch} and @water{100%ml} to the pan. Stir to combine, bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}, until slightly thickened.

Once thickened, stir half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a knob of @?butter{} through the lentils until combined. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When ready, divide your lentil filling between the roasted pepper halves.

Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the cheese is golden and the peppers are soft, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Once the roasted garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin into a small #bowl{} and mash with a #fork{}.

Add the coriander and lime zest to the mashed garlic. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{1%pinch}. Squeeze in half the lime juice and stir through the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the salsa. Set aside.

Squeeze the remaining lime juice into a medium #bowl{}. Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the dressing and toss to coat.

Share the stuffed peppers, chips and salad between your plates. Spoon the coriander salsa over the peppers to finish.

Enjoy!

> Our Peri Peri Spiced Stuffed Pepper and Chips is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!